 I studied for two years with a sculptor up in Hempstead,

129
00:05:32,640 --> 00:05:34,260
 and we were working together.

130
00:05:34,260 --> 00:05:35,720
 And at one point, she said,

131
00:05:35,720 --> 00:05:37,580
 I think your sketching and drawing is pretty good,

132
00:05:37,580 --> 00:05:38,880
 but it needs to be better.

133
00:05:38,880 --> 00:05:42,680
 And so I went to the Sam Martin School of Art,

134
00:05:42,680 --> 00:05:46,240
 couple of art classes there on sketching and drawing,

135
00:05:46,240 --> 00:05:49,080
 particularly the portraits.

136
00:05:49,080 --> 00:05:52,400
 So in that class, and you have to kind of imagine this,

137
00:05:52,400 --> 00:05:54,560
 it was in San Martin, it was second floor,

138
00:05:54,560 --> 00:05:57,320
 and it was this beautiful light room.

139
00:05:57,320 --> 00:05:58,680
 It wasn't very big.

140
00:05:58,680 --> 00:06:00,040
 There were eight of us students in there,

141
00:06:00,040 --> 00:06:02,760
