177
00:07:39,520 --> 00:07:43,740
 When Pastor Andrew was closing up the series on Psalm 27,

178
00:07:43,740 --> 00:07:48,240
 and waiting, he was looking at the last verses

179
00:07:48,240 --> 00:07:52,000
 where it says, "I will see the goodness

180
00:07:52,000 --> 00:07:53,760
 "in the land of the living."

181
00:07:53,760 --> 00:07:56,160
 And he was talking about with a lot of social media,

182
00:07:56,160 --> 00:07:58,480
 a lot of with just news media,

183
00:07:58,480 --> 00:08:00,280
 all the news that's going on,

184
00:08:00,280 --> 00:08:02,920
 it can paint a very dark world.

185
00:08:02,920 --> 00:08:06,200
 And it can paint a very uncertain and hard place.

186
00:08:06,200 --> 00:08:11,200
 But there is beauty for those who have eyes to see.

187
00:08:11,320 --> 00:08:13,780
 There is beauty all around us.

188
00:08:13,780 --> 00:08:16,200
 There's to the left of us and to the right of us.

189
00:08:16,200 --> 00:08:18,660
 But do we have eyes to see?

190
00:08:18,660 --> 00:08:19,960
 That's what we're gonna be talking about

191
00:08:19,960 --> 00:08:22,200
 as we look at our passage today.

192
00:08:22,200 --> 00:08:24,700
 So we're gonna look at a short passage.

193
00:08:24,700 --> 00:08:25,940
 It comes in the book of Mark.

194
00:08:25,940 --> 00:08:30,540
 It's Mark 8, begins 22 and then goes to verse 26.

195
00:08:30,540 --> 00:08:33,860
 It's a healing of a blind man.

196
00:08:33,860 --> 00:08:36,360
 You can see it there and I'll just read it for us.

197
00:08:36,360 --> 00:08:40,300
 And they came to Bethsaida.

198
00:08:40,300 --> 00:08:44,100
 And some people brought to him a blind man

199
00:08:44,100 --> 00:08:46,900
 and begged him to touch him.

200
00:08:46,900 --> 00:08:49,940
 Okay, the they there is Jesus and his disciples.

201
00:08:49,940 --> 00:08:51,480
 They'd been on the other side of the lake.

202
00:08:51,480 --> 00:08:55,220
 They came to Bethsaida, northeast side of the Sea of Galilee.

203
00:08:55,220 --> 00:08:57,460
 So they is Jesus and his disciples.

204
00:08:57,460 --> 00:09:01,020
 Bethsaida, hometown of several of the disciples.

205
00:09:01,020 --> 00:09:04,520
 And the some people brought a blind man.

206
00:09:04,520 --> 00:09:06,420
 Now, there's not a specific group.

207
00:09:06,420 --> 00:09:08,400
 Sometimes we'll read in the Gospels,

208
00:09:08,400 --> 00:09:10,220
 there's the Pharisees or there's a whatever.

209
00:09:10,220 --> 00:09:13,780
 This is just some people and it's a blind man.

210
00:09:13,780 --> 00:09:15,860
 So the specifics are not in the individual.

211
00:09:15,860 --> 00:09:19,500
 Specific is in what's about to happen.

212
00:09:19,500 --> 00:09:21,500
 So if we look at what's about to happen,

213
00:09:21,500 --> 00:09:25,380
 it says, "And Jesus took the blind man by the hand

214
00:09:25,380 --> 00:09:27,260
 "and he led him out of the village.

215
00:09:27,260 --> 00:09:28,800
 "And when he had spit on his eyes

216
00:09:28,800 --> 00:09:31,620
 "and laid his hands on him, he asked him,

217
00:09:31,620 --> 00:09:32,820
 "Do you see anything?

218
00:09:32,820 --> 00:09:35,740
 "And the man looked up and said,

219
00:09:35,740 --> 00:09:40,020
 "I see people, but they look like trees walking.

220
00:09:40,020 --> 00:09:42,740
 "And then Jesus laid his hands on his eyes again

221
00:09:42,740 --> 00:09:44,660
 "and he opened his eyes.

222
00:09:44,660 --> 00:09:49,580
 "His sight was restored and he saw everything clearly.

223
00:09:49,580 --> 00:09:52,900
 "And he sent, and Jesus sent him to his home saying,

224
00:09:52,900 --> 00:09:57,900
 "Do not even enter the village."

225
00:09:57,900 --> 00:09:59,200
 Okay, so that's our text.

226
00:09:59,200 --> 00:10:01,100
 That's what happened.

227
00:10:01,100 --> 00:10:04,860
 So what I wanna offer us today is a little model

228
00:10:04,860 --> 00:10:07,420
 that we used at the University of Hong Kong

229
00:10:07,420 --> 00:10:09,060
 with the Character Leadership Program

230
00:10:09,060 --> 00:10:10,660
 that Andrew was talking about

231
00:10:10,660 --> 00:10:14,300
 to help our students reflect on what had happened

232
00:10:14,300 --> 00:10:16,100
 and the importance of what had happened.

233
00:10:16,100 --> 00:10:19,660
 And the model I wanna share with you is by Driscoll.

234
00:10:19,660 --> 00:10:21,300
 It's a model of reflective practice.

235
00:10:21,300 --> 00:10:23,540
 It's basically the three what model.

236
00:10:23,540 --> 00:10:27,380
 What or what happened, so what, and then now what?

237
00:10:27,380 --> 00:10:30,720
 And I like it because it doesn't just focus

238
00:10:30,720 --> 00:10:34,420
 on the what happened and so what and stay there.

239
00:10:34,420 --> 00:10:37,500
 The focus is on the future because that's why we reflect.

240
00:10:37,500 --> 00:10:39,820
 That's also why we reflect on the Bible

241
00:10:39,820 --> 00:10:41,500
 because Jesus says, "Blessed are those

242
00:10:41,500 --> 00:10:45,260
 "who don't only hear or read the word, but they do it."

243
00:10:45,260 --> 00:10:48,260
 So we're getting to the now what.

244
00:10:48,260 --> 00:10:51,420
 And so actually if you're a community group leader

245
00:10:51,420 --> 00:10:53,380
 or lead Bible studies

246
00:10:53,380 --> 00:10:55,140
 or even for your own personal devotion,

247
00:10:55,140 --> 00:10:56,340
 it's a good pattern.

248
00:10:56,340 --> 00:10:57,980
 So I'm just gonna use that today.

249
00:10:57,980 --> 00:11:00,820
 We've already looked at the first what or what happened.

250
00:11:00,820 --> 00:11:02,980
 So now we're gonna go on to the so what.

251
00:11:04,080 --> 00:11:08,120
 The so what in this passage, right away,

252
00:11:08,120 --> 00:11:09,680
 there's something very subtle,

253
00:11:09,680 --> 00:11:14,680
 but something very beautiful that it teaches us about Jesus.

254
00:11:14,680 --> 00:11:18,880
 And that something comes in what Jesus does

255
00:11:18,880 --> 00:11:22,440
 when he takes the man by the hand, it says,

256
00:11:22,440 --> 00:11:25,160
 and he leads him out of the village.

257
00:11:25,160 --> 00:11:27,960
 Yes, the village Bethsaida was a hometown

258
00:11:27,960 --> 00:11:29,320
 and a son of the disciples,

259
00:11:29,320 --> 00:11:33,480
 but it was known more because there was a challenge,

260
00:11:33,480 --> 00:11:36,640
 a challenge Jesus' authority and power.

261
00:11:36,640 --> 00:11:39,920
 So in Matthew 11, 21, we read this,

262
00:11:39,920 --> 00:11:44,920
 "Woe to you, Bethsaida, for if the mighty works done in you

263
00:11:44,920 --> 00:11:47,620
 "had been done in Tyre and Sidon,

264
00:11:47,620 --> 00:11:52,400
 "they would have repented in sackcloth and ashes."

265
00:11:52,400 --> 00:11:55,620
 So what's happening here is this Jesus saying,

266
00:11:55,620 --> 00:11:57,860
 "Yeah, I will heal you,

267
00:11:57,860 --> 00:11:59,960
 "but I'm not gonna do it here in the village.

268
00:11:59,960 --> 00:12:03,740
 "Let's go out to a quiet place

269
00:12:03,740 --> 00:12:06,520
 "because this is not a healing show.

270
00:12:06,520 --> 00:12:08,220
 "This is not a spectacle.

271
00:12:08,220 --> 00:12:10,900
 "I'm not gonna get you involved in all the controversy

272
00:12:10,900 --> 00:12:13,000
 "between those who are criticizing me

273
00:12:13,000 --> 00:12:15,080
 "and you get caught up in all of that.

274
00:12:15,080 --> 00:12:17,960
 "You need to see, I will heal you."

275
00:12:17,960 --> 00:12:20,600
 And he does it in this beautifully,

276
00:12:20,600 --> 00:12:23,760
 compassionate, respectful way.

277
00:12:23,760 --> 00:12:27,440
 And that's Jesus, that's our Jesus, that's what he does.

278
00:12:27,440 --> 00:12:28,620
 If you're here this morning,

279
00:12:28,620 --> 00:12:30,780
 you have something as we were going through,

280
00:12:30,780 --> 00:12:33,180
 praying through the blood and Andrew was leading us

281
00:12:33,180 --> 00:12:34,960
 and there was something there,

282
00:12:34,960 --> 00:12:36,960
 you can bring that right to him

283
00:12:36,960 --> 00:12:41,580
 and know he will meet you with love and respect.

284
00:12:41,580 --> 00:12:42,960
 That's who he is.

285
00:12:42,960 --> 00:12:46,640
 God is love-loving, that's all it is.

286
00:12:46,640 --> 00:12:48,400
 So that's the first thing that we can see in this

287
00:12:48,400 --> 00:12:49,680
 and we can draw comfort on it.

288
00:12:49,680 --> 00:12:51,720
 And let me say, if you're feeling that,

289
00:12:51,720 --> 00:12:54,880
 what I just said had an impact on you,

290
00:12:54,880 --> 00:12:56,120
 then don't lose that.

291
00:12:56,120 --> 00:13:00,320
 Stay with that thought and go and take that to Jesus already

292
00:13:00,320 --> 00:13:02,920
 and then later we'll have some more time to do that.

293
00:13:02,920 --> 00:13:06,740
 Second thing, little more stark

294
00:13:06,740 --> 00:13:09,280
 and that is the two-stage healing.

295
00:13:09,280 --> 00:13:10,700
 So this is very unusual

296
00:13:10,700 --> 00:13:13,980
 because you don't see this in any other healing stories.

297
00:13:13,980 --> 00:13:17,500
 But right in the middle there where Jesus is healing him,

298
00:13:17,500 --> 00:13:20,860
 he spits on his eye, which is kind of a common

299
00:13:20,860 --> 00:13:23,420
 or a customary healing practice at the time.

300
00:13:23,420 --> 00:13:25,700
 Then he lays his hands on him and he says,

301
00:13:25,700 --> 00:13:27,140
 do you see anything?

302
00:13:27,140 --> 00:13:29,480
 And the man says, I see people,

303
00:13:29,480 --> 00:13:31,380
 but they look like trees walking.

304
00:13:31,380 --> 00:13:35,980
 And then Jesus touches him a second time and he heals him.

305
00:13:35,980 --> 00:13:40,180
 And then what it says is here is his eyes were opened.

306
00:13:40,180 --> 00:13:42,620
 It's this word diablepo.

307
00:13:42,620 --> 00:13:46,540
 His sight was restored and he saw everything clearly.

308
00:13:46,540 --> 00:13:49,940
 This diablepo has this meaning of it was opened,

309
00:13:49,940 --> 00:13:52,700
 but it's also this meaning of engaged intent.

310
00:13:52,700 --> 00:13:55,060
 That when you see, it's like coming to life

311
00:13:55,060 --> 00:13:59,620
 and the light has come into the man and he can see.

312
00:13:59,620 --> 00:14:03,260
 Now, the question is,

313
00:14:03,260 --> 00:14:07,540
 why did it have to be a two-stage healing there, right?

314
00:14:07,540 --> 00:14:09,980
 Was it just a bad day for Jesus?

315
00:14:09,980 --> 00:14:11,380
 Was Jesus kind of tired

316
00:14:11,380 --> 00:14:14,420
 and it took like two shots at it or anything?

317
00:14:14,420 --> 00:14:16,580
 And the answer is no.

318
00:14:16,580 --> 00:14:19,240
 Jesus, if you look through all of the miracle healing,

319
00:14:19,240 --> 00:14:21,000
 sometimes he didn't even have to be there

320
00:14:21,000 --> 00:14:22,380
 and the person was healed.

321
00:14:22,380 --> 00:14:24,780
 Sometimes he said a word, sometimes he didn't said a word,

322
00:14:24,780 --> 00:14:28,660
 sometimes, it's not about Jesus healing here,

323
00:14:28,660 --> 00:14:32,940
 but it is about who Jesus is.

324
00:14:32,940 --> 00:14:35,700
 And I think maybe a little bit about the person.

325
00:14:35,700 --> 00:14:36,540
 I don't know about you,

326
00:14:36,540 --> 00:14:39,140
 but I find the two healing very attractive

327
00:14:39,140 --> 00:14:44,140
 'cause often, usually, I need at least two touches from God

328
00:14:44,140 --> 00:14:47,140
 before I can see something clearly, right?

329
00:14:47,140 --> 00:14:48,140
 And God does that.

330
00:14:48,140 --> 00:14:50,520
 He will take as many times as it needs.

331
00:14:50,520 --> 00:14:53,080
 But this particular two-step,

332
00:14:53,080 --> 00:14:55,380
 there's something deeper going on.

333
00:14:55,380 --> 00:14:58,420
 And this something deeper has to do

334
00:14:58,420 --> 00:15:00,660
 with the songs we were just singing

335
00:15:00,660 --> 00:15:03,900
 about the cross and about the blood

336
00:15:03,900 --> 00:15:06,500
 and about the cost and about Jesus' love

337
00:15:06,500 --> 00:15:09,800
 and about all he gave for all of us.

338
00:15:09,800 --> 00:15:13,740
 Now, we need to go deeper,

339
00:15:13,740 --> 00:15:15,340
 but to go deeper, we need to go wider

340
00:15:15,340 --> 00:15:18,020
 and look briefly at the passage before

341
00:15:18,020 --> 00:15:20,420
 and then the passage after, and then we can understand.

342
00:15:20,420 --> 00:15:22,380
 If you've been studying Bible any length of time,

343
00:15:22,380 --> 00:15:24,000
 you know that context is everything.

344
00:15:24,000 --> 00:15:27,720
 This is a great passage that shows the power of context.

345
00:15:27,720 --> 00:15:29,140
 So if you look at the first,

346
00:15:29,140 --> 00:15:31,360
 the passage that came right before it,

347
00:15:31,360 --> 00:15:33,880
 Jesus and disciples are on the other side of the lake

348
00:15:33,880 --> 00:15:36,280
 and they have the feeding of the 4,000.

349
00:15:36,280 --> 00:15:37,580
 It's an amazing miracle.

350
00:15:37,580 --> 00:15:42,580
 4,000 people and others are fed in that miracle.

351
00:15:42,580 --> 00:15:45,160
 At the end of that miracle, as oftentimes,

352
00:15:45,160 --> 00:15:48,680
 after a healing or a beautiful miracle, Jesus is attacked.

353
00:15:48,680 --> 00:15:51,360
 So people were coming and they were criticizing him.

354
00:15:51,360 --> 00:15:53,960
 He has an altercation with the Pharisees

355
00:15:53,960 --> 00:15:55,560
 and so they decide to get in the boat

356
00:15:55,560 --> 00:15:57,560
 and go over here to Bethsaida.

357
00:15:57,560 --> 00:15:58,400
 They get in the boat.

358
00:15:58,400 --> 00:16:01,480
 The disciples realized, "We didn't bring any food

359
00:16:01,480 --> 00:16:03,560
 "and we didn't bring any bread."

360
00:16:03,560 --> 00:16:05,680
 Now, you wouldn't think that would be a problem, right?

361
00:16:05,680 --> 00:16:07,520
 'Cause Jesus has just fed 4,000,

362
00:16:07,520 --> 00:16:08,700
 but they were worried about it.

363
00:16:08,700 --> 00:16:10,520
 And so Jesus gets in.

364
00:16:10,520 --> 00:16:13,540
 Jesus is still thinking about the conversation he had

365
00:16:13,540 --> 00:16:16,080
 with the Pharisees and he says to his followers,

366
00:16:16,080 --> 00:16:20,540
 he says, "Beware of the leaven of the Pharisees."

367
00:16:20,540 --> 00:16:23,960
 Now, what we know now is that leaven is,

368
00:16:23,960 --> 00:16:25,000
 it's about the teaching.

369
00:16:25,000 --> 00:16:27,520
 Beware of the teaching because bad teaching

370
00:16:27,520 --> 00:16:31,160
 can get into a community like leaven and bread

371
00:16:31,160 --> 00:16:33,720
 and spread throughout and it can cause

372
00:16:33,720 --> 00:16:35,640
 all types of problems.

373
00:16:35,640 --> 00:16:36,880
 So Jesus is saying that.

374
00:16:36,880 --> 00:16:39,200
 The disciples think, "Oh, he said leaven.

375
00:16:39,200 --> 00:16:40,140
 "We forgot the bread.

376
00:16:40,140 --> 00:16:43,480
 "Jesus is upset with us because we forgot the bread."

377
00:16:43,480 --> 00:16:44,840
 And I love this about the disciples

378
00:16:44,840 --> 00:16:47,240
 and I also love that they wrote it about themselves

379
00:16:47,240 --> 00:16:49,320
 because so often we're in the same boat

380
00:16:49,320 --> 00:16:50,480
 with the disciples, right?

381
00:16:50,480 --> 00:16:53,440
 And here's what Jesus says to them after that.

382
00:16:53,440 --> 00:16:57,440
 He says, "Do you not yet perceive or understand?

383
00:16:57,440 --> 00:16:59,760
 "Are your hearts hardened?

384
00:16:59,760 --> 00:17:02,320
 "Having eyes, do you not see?"

385
00:17:02,320 --> 00:17:06,640
 And then at the very end, "Do you not yet understand?"

386
00:17:06,640 --> 00:17:11,640
 That's how we enter into this teaching today.

387
00:17:11,640 --> 00:17:13,540
 That's what comes right before.

388
00:17:13,540 --> 00:17:16,360
 Now we have to look at what comes afterwards.

389
00:17:16,360 --> 00:17:19,600
 You look afterwards, there's this beautiful exchange

390
00:17:19,600 --> 00:17:23,280
 where Jesus' fame is growing.

391
00:17:23,280 --> 00:17:25,040
 People are talking about him all over the place.

392
00:17:25,040 --> 00:17:27,500
 And so Jesus says to his disciples, he says,

393
00:17:27,500 --> 00:17:29,040
 "Who do people say that I am?"

394
00:17:29,040 --> 00:17:31,960
 And some say Isaiah, some say John the Baptist.

395
00:17:31,960 --> 00:17:33,680
 And he said, "Who do you say I am?"

396
00:17:33,680 --> 00:17:37,240
 And that's, of course, the key question of our faith

397
00:17:37,240 --> 00:17:39,560
 is who do you say Jesus is?

398
00:17:39,560 --> 00:17:43,160
 And then Peter nails it.

399
00:17:43,160 --> 00:17:45,400
 He says, "You're the Christ."

400
00:17:45,400 --> 00:17:50,200
 Okay, that's the first sign of seeing.

401
00:17:50,200 --> 00:17:51,760
 They didn't have eyes, they didn't see.

402
00:17:51,760 --> 00:17:55,480
 Now he sees you're the Messiah, you're the Christ.

403
00:17:55,480 --> 00:17:58,780
 But then just a few passages after that,

404
00:17:58,780 --> 00:18:01,400
 then Jesus is talking about he must suffer.

405
00:18:01,400 --> 00:18:03,920
 And Peter says, "No, that's not what a Messiah does."

406
00:18:03,920 --> 00:18:07,280
 And then Jesus says to Peter, "Get behind me, Satan."

407
00:18:07,280 --> 00:18:10,000
 In other words, he hasn't seen fully.

408
00:18:10,000 --> 00:18:11,900
 He hasn't seen fully.

409
00:18:11,900 --> 00:18:16,080
 Now we begin to see a little bit of what Mark and Jesus

410
00:18:16,080 --> 00:18:17,560
 is trying to teach his disciples.

411
00:18:17,560 --> 00:18:19,240
 They're part of the they right there,

412
00:18:19,240 --> 00:18:22,080
 but also what Mark is trying to see, show us,

413
00:18:22,080 --> 00:18:25,020
 and teach us, this full vision.

414
00:18:25,020 --> 00:18:30,020
 Because the full vision of Jesus involves the cross.

415
00:18:30,020 --> 00:18:32,200
 And so Jesus would later say,

416
00:18:32,200 --> 00:18:36,040
 "If anyone would come after me, let him deny himself

417
00:18:36,040 --> 00:18:39,400
 "and take up the cross and follow me."

418
00:18:39,400 --> 00:18:40,460
 Does that make sense?

419
00:18:41,880 --> 00:18:46,880
 Okay, this is not Jesus says, "Yes, you can feed

420
00:18:46,880 --> 00:18:50,340
 "4,000 people, you're going to be a very useful person

421
00:18:50,340 --> 00:18:52,580
 "when we have picnics and we have dinners

422
00:18:52,580 --> 00:18:53,920
 "and we have all of these things

423
00:18:53,920 --> 00:18:57,080
 "that you can give us," right?

424
00:18:57,080 --> 00:18:58,920
 It's gonna be the cross.

425
00:18:58,920 --> 00:19:02,000
 And it's gonna be about us taking up the cross.

426
00:19:02,000 --> 00:19:03,540
 This is about discipleship.

427
00:19:03,540 --> 00:19:09,780
 But the same message is that Jesus wants us

428
00:19:10,020 --> 00:19:14,440
 and his disciples to see, to see fully.

429
00:19:14,440 --> 00:19:20,280
 How are we doing?

430
00:19:20,280 --> 00:19:21,120
 How's this going?

431
00:19:21,120 --> 00:19:24,700
 All right, doing okay?

432
00:19:24,700 --> 00:19:27,560
 Yeah, should we all get up and dance and say,

433
00:19:27,560 --> 00:19:31,300
 "Beauty to the left of me, beauty to the right."

434
00:19:31,300 --> 00:19:32,660
 We might do, no thank you.

435
00:19:32,660 --> 00:19:36,180
 Afterwards maybe, and we can do a special dance.

436
00:19:36,180 --> 00:19:41,060
 But I wanna be clear here,

437
00:19:41,060 --> 00:19:42,780
 and I don't want you to get me wrong,

438
00:19:42,780 --> 00:19:46,400
 that when you have this full vision of God,

439
00:19:46,400 --> 00:19:49,380
 it's all about suffering because it's not.

440
00:19:49,380 --> 00:19:53,460
 It's all about life and it's about love.

441
00:19:53,460 --> 00:19:57,660
 And when you have that encounter where Jesus says,

442
00:19:57,660 --> 00:20:01,580
 "I wanna give you a full picture of myself,"

443
00:20:01,580 --> 00:20:03,920
 there's beauty all around us.

444
00:20:03,920 --> 00:20:08,300
 I remember as a 17-year-old, northern Nigeria, Zaria,

445
00:20:08,300 --> 00:20:11,980
 one night having an encounter with Jesus Christ.

446
00:20:11,980 --> 00:20:15,540
 And in that moment of just seeing God,

447
00:20:15,540 --> 00:20:17,800
 who I'd heard about all my life,

448
00:20:17,800 --> 00:20:21,180
 for who he was and the love he had for us,

449
00:20:21,180 --> 00:20:26,180
 just remember feeling like energy and joy and light.

450
00:20:26,180 --> 00:20:29,820
 And I saw things differently

451
00:20:29,820 --> 00:20:33,500
 because I saw Jesus for who he was.

452
00:20:33,500 --> 00:20:38,500
 And that's open to all of us, to see Jesus in that way.

453
00:20:38,500 --> 00:20:43,820
 But it also, as soon as we begin to see Jesus

454
00:20:43,820 --> 00:20:46,880
 for who we are, for who he is,

455
00:20:46,880 --> 00:20:48,900
 as soon as we begin to see Jesus for who he is,

456
00:20:48,900 --> 00:20:52,980
 it helps us understand some of our own suffering.

457
00:20:52,980 --> 00:20:57,780
 Because beauty can come through very difficult times.

458
00:20:57,780 --> 00:21:01,180
 We see that in everything.

459
00:21:01,180 --> 00:21:02,780
 Tim Keller says this.

460
00:21:02,780 --> 00:21:04,420
 Tim Keller, in his book, he says,

461
00:21:04,420 --> 00:21:06,000
 "I can think," it's a book on prayer,

462
00:21:06,000 --> 00:21:10,620
 "I can think of nothing great that is also easy."

463
00:21:10,620 --> 00:21:13,100
 And he's talking about how hard prayer is,

464
00:21:13,100 --> 00:21:16,800
 but that out of that comes this beautiful beauty

465
00:21:16,800 --> 00:21:19,540
 and flourishing and greatness.

466
00:21:19,540 --> 00:21:21,020
 And I think that's true

467
00:21:21,020 --> 00:21:23,060
 if we think about it in our lives as well.

468
00:21:23,060 --> 00:21:24,860
 It's definitely true in Jesus' life.

469
00:21:24,860 --> 00:21:28,300
 If you've not decided to go ahead

470
00:21:28,300 --> 00:21:29,740
 and read the Gospel of John,

471
00:21:29,740 --> 00:21:31,860
 along with some of the other international churches

472
00:21:31,860 --> 00:21:35,500
 and local churches here in Hong Kong for Lent,

473
00:21:35,500 --> 00:21:36,540
 I recommend it to you.

474
00:21:36,540 --> 00:21:38,020
 Basically, the church is just reading through,

475
00:21:38,020 --> 00:21:38,940
 it's called the One Campaign,

476
00:21:38,940 --> 00:21:40,680
 just reading through the Gospels.

477
00:21:40,680 --> 00:21:42,580
 I've been reading them through John.

478
00:21:42,580 --> 00:21:44,260
 It's good if you don't wanna read through John,

479
00:21:44,260 --> 00:21:45,980
 read through a Gospel.

480
00:21:45,980 --> 00:21:49,280
 This year, at least read through one Gospel.

481
00:21:49,280 --> 00:21:50,700
 And if we're gonna follow Jesus Christ,

482
00:21:50,700 --> 00:21:54,420
 we need to read the texts that mainly talk about him, amen?

483
00:21:54,420 --> 00:21:56,340
 And if you wanna read four, that's even better,

484
00:21:56,340 --> 00:21:57,980
 because you'll get stories like this

485
00:21:57,980 --> 00:22:00,820
 that aren't in the other Gospels, right?

486
00:22:00,820 --> 00:22:03,700
 But as we read, what we're gonna find is this.

487
00:22:03,700 --> 00:22:06,500
 It's almost like every day was a Monday for Jesus.

488
00:22:06,500 --> 00:22:08,620
 Every day was a tough day, right?

489
00:22:08,620 --> 00:22:11,540
 Every day, he's doing these amazing things.

490
00:22:11,540 --> 00:22:12,780
 He's healing people,

491
00:22:12,780 --> 00:22:15,240
 where people should be standing up and cheering,

492
00:22:15,240 --> 00:22:16,180
 but they're not.

493
00:22:16,180 --> 00:22:18,620
 They're coming and saying, "Why do you do that?

494
00:22:18,620 --> 00:22:19,960
 "By what right do you do that?

495
00:22:19,960 --> 00:22:20,800
 "Who are you?"

496
00:22:20,800 --> 00:22:25,800
 And there's this attacking and testing all the time, right?

497
00:22:25,800 --> 00:22:27,540
 But here's something that beautiful,

498
00:22:27,540 --> 00:22:29,700
 as that happens in that testing,

499
00:22:29,700 --> 00:22:31,780
 beauty comes out of it.

500
00:22:31,780 --> 00:22:35,300
 Just one example where one day, a lawyer came,

501
00:22:35,300 --> 00:22:38,900
 and the text tells us he came to test Jesus.

502
00:22:38,900 --> 00:22:41,020
 And he said, "What's the greatest commandment?"

503
00:22:41,020 --> 00:22:43,500
 And Jesus gives this beautiful response

504
00:22:43,500 --> 00:22:45,740
 that resonates today,

505
00:22:45,740 --> 00:22:47,700
 and that can get you through this day,

506
00:22:47,700 --> 00:22:51,020
 and that is love God, love others, love yourself.

507
00:22:51,020 --> 00:22:52,300
 That's what life's about.

508
00:22:52,300 --> 00:22:55,580
 And that came out of a time of testing

509
00:22:55,580 --> 00:22:57,600
 with great, great beauty.

510
00:22:58,860 --> 00:23:00,780
 So my prayer today is this,

511
00:23:00,780 --> 00:23:03,180
 that we would just pray,

512
00:23:03,180 --> 00:23:06,140
 God, enlarge our vision,

513
00:23:06,140 --> 00:23:08,100
 and open our eyes.

514
00:23:08,100 --> 00:23:12,400
 We do not want to see you partially.

515
00:23:12,400 --> 00:23:14,440
 We don't want a partial sight of God.

516
00:23:14,440 --> 00:23:15,900
 We want to see the full,

517
00:23:15,900 --> 00:23:17,740
 whatever we can contain,

518
00:23:17,740 --> 00:23:18,620
 whatever we can hold,

519
00:23:18,620 --> 00:23:20,540
 and we know we can't maybe hold all of it.

520
00:23:20,540 --> 00:23:23,900
 We want to see all of you, Jesus,

521
00:23:23,900 --> 00:23:27,440
 because when we do that,

522
00:23:27,440 --> 00:23:30,040
 it's gonna help our relationship with others.

523
00:23:30,040 --> 00:23:32,380
 Now we're gonna go a little deeper, okay?

524
00:23:32,380 --> 00:23:34,060
 Because here's what I found.

