00:25:02,800 --> 00:25:05,060
 of pudding or dessert or whatever we say,

558
00:25:05,060 --> 00:25:06,620
 that's a healthy portion, right?

559
00:25:06,620 --> 00:25:09,580
 Or that's a generous portion, that's a gracious portion.

560
00:25:09,580 --> 00:25:13,460
 That's the eyes of the Father when he looks on us.

561
00:25:13,460 --> 00:25:18,460
 And when we have a whole view of how God sees,

562
00:25:18,460 --> 00:25:23,780
 then we tend to see the others with a healthy perspective,

563
00:25:23,780 --> 00:25:25,220
 a healthy situation.

564
00:25:25,220 --> 00:25:30,220
 But if we have a distorted vision,

565
00:25:30,220 --> 00:25:33,760
 if our eye is not healthy, not gracious, not whatever,

566
00:25:33,760 --> 00:25:38,380
 then we're going to see things in a distorted way.

567
00:25:38,380 --> 00:25:39,500
 We're gonna see it at the level

568
00:25:39,500 --> 00:25:41,660
 of people walking around like trees.

569
00:25:41,660 --> 00:25:43,660
 They're kind of objects and distorted.

570
00:25:43,660 --> 00:25:45,120
 And maybe we see them as enemies

571
00:25:45,120 --> 00:25:46,820
 or maybe someone to overcome

572
00:25:46,820 --> 00:25:48,140
 or someone that's getting in our way

573
00:25:48,140 --> 00:25:50,300
 or someone that annoys us or someone to,

574
00:25:50,300 --> 00:25:53,440
 whatever it is, that's how we view a situation

575
00:25:53,440 --> 00:25:56,680
 or people, and the consequence is

576
00:25:56,680 --> 00:25:59,900
 our body becomes full of darkness, right?

577
00:25:59,900 --> 00:26:04,180
 Then we have this regret, this we have this anger,

578
00:26:04,180 --> 00:26:07,900
 then we have this whatever's going on in that relationship.

579
00:26:07,900 --> 00:26:12,500
 So here's my cry for us today is that we would go to Jesus

