00:27:45,640 --> 00:27:47,520
 He's gonna see him again.

614
00:27:47,520 --> 00:27:49,340
 He's gonna take another look.

615
00:27:49,340 --> 00:27:51,700
 He's gonna try to take a healthy vision.

616
00:27:51,700 --> 00:27:55,240
 And I wonder if that's the case with us as well,

617
00:27:55,240 --> 00:27:58,080
 in some of the situations we find ourselves in.

618
00:27:58,080 --> 00:28:07,320
 There's a beautiful story that is a rabbinic tale,

619
00:28:07,320 --> 00:28:10,840
 and I think it's a tale of our times.

620
00:28:10,840 --> 00:28:12,460
 And the rabbinic tale goes like this.

621
00:28:12,460 --> 00:28:14,380
 Usually with rabbinic tales, they're about rabbis,

622
00:28:14,380 --> 00:28:15,900
 and they're kind of fun tales,

623
00:28:15,900 --> 00:28:18,900
 but the rabbi is walking with his students.

624
00:28:18,900 --> 00:28:20,140
 And he's walking his students.

625
00:28:20,140 --> 00:28:22,580
 It's basically a style of teaching where you just walk out,

626
00:28:22,580 --> 00:28:24,020
 and then you ask questions,

627
00:28:24,020 --> 00:28:25,380
 Socratic methods to the students.

628
00:28:25,380 --> 00:28:26,500
 The students respond.

629
