00:29:09,820 --> 00:29:11,660
 "is it when I can look in the distance

648
00:29:11,660 --> 00:29:15,300
 "and then tell the difference between a fig tree

649
00:29:15,300 --> 00:29:20,300
 "and an olive tree, then I know that the night has gone

650
00:29:20,300 --> 00:29:22,260
 "and the morning has come?"

651
00:29:22,260 --> 00:29:23,600
 And the rabbi says, "No."

652
00:29:23,600 --> 00:29:26,480
 And so then they say, "Tell us, Rabbi,

653
00:29:26,480 --> 00:29:29,960
 "how can we know that the night has come,

654
00:29:29,960 --> 00:29:32,660
 "night has gone and the morning has come?"

655
00:29:32,660 --> 00:29:34,300
 And the rabbi says this.

